src="https://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/4.0/88x31.png"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 06 Jun 2024 11:42:27 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Si el límite de la sucesión uₙ es a, entonces el límite de -uₙ es -a</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/06-limite_de_la_opuesta/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;En Lean4, una sucesión \(u₀, u₁, u₂, ...\) se puede representar mediante una función \(u : ℕ → ℝ\) de forma que \(u(n)\) es \(uₙ\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Se define que \(c\) es el límite de la sucesión \(u\), por&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;   &lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kt"&gt;Prop&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
     &lt;span class="k"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;↦&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;N&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;N&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 que que si el límite de \(u_n\) es \(a\), entonces el de \(-u_n\) es \(-a\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Tactic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kt"&gt;Prop&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="k"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;↦&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;N&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;N&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;h&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;↦&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/06-limite_de_la_opuesta/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 3 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/06-limite_de_la_opuesta/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jun 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Si uₙ está acotada y el límite de vₙ es 0, entonces el límite de uₙ·vₙ es 0</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/03-producto_de_una_sucesion_acotada_por_otra_convergente_a_cero/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 que si \(u_n\) está acotada y el límite de \(v_n\) es \(0\), entonces el límite de \(u_n·v_n\) es \(0\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Tactic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;acotada&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;B&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hU&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;acotada&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hV&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/03-producto_de_una_sucesion_acotada_por_otra_convergente_a_cero/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 8 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/06/03-producto_de_una_sucesion_acotada_por_otra_convergente_a_cero/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 03 Jun 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Si (∀n)[uₙ ≤ vₙ], entonces lim uₙ ≤ lim vₙ</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/31-limite_de_sucesion_menor_que_otra_sucesion/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;En Lean4, una sucesión \(u_0, u_1, u_2, \dots\) se puede representar mediante una función \(u : ℕ → ℝ\) de forma que \(u(n)\) es el \(n\)-ésimo término de la sucesión.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Se define que \(a\) límite de la sucesión \(u\) como sigue&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;   &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="w"&gt;     &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Demostrar que si \((∀ n)[u_n ≤ v_n]\), \(a\) es límite de \(u_n\) y \(c\) es límite de \(v_n\), entonces \(a ≤ c\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hu&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hv&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;huv&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/31-limite_de_sucesion_menor_que_otra_sucesion/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 11 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/31-limite_de_sucesion_menor_que_otra_sucesion/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 31 May 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Las sucesiones convergentes están acotadas</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/28-acotacion_de_convergentes/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 que si \(u_n\) es una sucesión convergente, entonces está acotada; es decir,
\[ (∃ k ∈ ℕ)(∃ b ∈ ℝ)(∀ n ∈ ℕ)[n ≥ k → |u_n| ≤ b] \]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Tactic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="c1"&gt;-- (limite u c) expresa que el límite de u es c.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="c1"&gt;-- (convergente u) expresa que u es convergente.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;convergente&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;h&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;convergente&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;b&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;b&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/28-acotacion_de_convergentes/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 4 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/28-acotacion_de_convergentes/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 28 May 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Los supremos de las sucesiones crecientes son sus límites</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/24-los_supremos_de_las_sucesiones_crecientes_son_sus_limites/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sea \(u\) una sucesión creciente. Demostrar con Lean4 que si \(S\) es un supremo de \(u\), entonces el límite de \(u\) es \(S\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="c1"&gt;-- (limite u c) expresa que el límite de u es c.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;m&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="c1"&gt;-- (supremo u S) expresa que el supremo de u es S.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;supremo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∧&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;k&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hu&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Monotone&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hS&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;supremo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;S&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/24-los_supremos_de_las_sucesiones_crecientes_son_sus_limites/"&gt;Leer más…&lt;/a&gt; (quedan 7 minutos de lectura)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><guid>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/05/24-los_supremos_de_las_sucesiones_crecientes_son_sus_limites/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 24 May 2024 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>Teorema del emparedado</title><link>https://jaalonso.github.io/calculemus/posts/2024/02/19-teorema_del_emparedado/</link><dc:creator>José A. Alonso</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Demostrar con Lean4 el teorema del emparedado.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para ello, completar la siguiente teoría de Lean4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;w&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;variable&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ℕ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ℝ&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;→&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="kt"&gt;Prop&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="k"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;↦&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∃&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;N&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≥&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;N&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ε&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="kd"&gt;example&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hu&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;hw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;w&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;h1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="o"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;h2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;∀&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;≤&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;w&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class="n"&gt;limite&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;v&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="kd"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="gr"&gt;sorry&lt;/span&gt;
